HEADWORD: Top-cloth
<hw>Top"-cloth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A piece of canvas used to cover the hammocks which are lashed to
the top in action to protect the topmen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topcoat</ent>⟦br⟧
